      section.bordered(data-name='layout')
        h2 Layout

        h3 .block
        p Sometimes you need to separate components vertically. Say in a form.

        .block
          label You might want to type something here.
          .editor.mini.editor-colors Something you typed...
        .block
          label.icon.icon-file-directory Another field with an icon
          .editor.mini.editor-colors Something else you typed...
        .block
          button.btn Do it

        h3 .inline-block
        p Sometimes you need to separate components horizontally.

        .block
          label This is a thing with stuff in it
          div
            .inline-block.editor.mini.editor-colors Something you typed...
            .inline-block.btn-group
              button.btn One
              button.btn Two

        .block
          button.inline-block.btn Do it
          button.inline-block.btn Another
          button.inline-block.btn OMG again

        h3 .inline-block-tight
        p You might want things to be a little closer to each other.

        .block
          button.inline-block-tight.btn Do it
          button.inline-block-tight.btn Another
          button.inline-block-tight.btn OMG again

      section.bordered(data-name='panels')
        h2 Panels
        p Useful when you want a block of content with a heading.

        h3 With a heading

        .panel
          .panel-heading A .panel heading
          .panel-body.padded Some Content goes here. I am padded!


        h3 Bordered with a heading
        p You can add the class <code>.bordered</code> to the panel to add a border.

        .panel.bordered
          .panel-heading A .panel heading
          .panel-body.padded Some Content goes here. I am padded!


      section.bordered(data-name='tool-panel')
        h2 Tool Panel
        p A container attached to some side of the Atom UI. This styleguide is in a tool panel.

        .tool-panel.panel-bottom.padded
          div Some content

        p Supports <code>.panel-bottom</code> and <code>.panel-left</code> classes.

      section.bordered(data-name='inset-panel')
        h2 Inset Panel
        p Use inside another panel, like a <code>.tool-panel</code>.

        h3 no-heading
        .tool-panel.panel-bottom.padded
          .inset-panel.padded Some content

        h3 heading
        .tool-panel.panel-bottom.padded
          .inset-panel
            .panel-heading An inset-panel heading
            .panel-body.padded Some Content


        h3 With buttons in the heading
